  "description": "<p>Snug as a bug in a rug...as long as the bug is you and the rug is the Space Cowboy +7C Sleeping Bag. A zoned design keeps your sleeping situation just right, giving you extra insulation on top where you need it and less on the bottom where your sleeping pad has you covered. A new lightweight shell and lining made with recycled materials, are both durable and eco-friendly. Synthetic fill stands up to morning dew, so you can \"cowboy camp\" under the stars without a tent.</p><ul><li>Lightweight, durable ripstop shell and liner made from recycled fabrics</li><li>Synthetic eraLoft\u2122 is efficient, compressible polyester that dries fast and retains warmth when wet. Hollow fibres reduce weight without sacrificing warmth</li><li>Zoned design provides maximum insulation where it's needed \u2013 on top. Your sleeping pad insulates you on the bottom, so the bag has less fill there to save weight</li><li>Removable SynergyLink\u2122 connectors integrate to your sleeping pad to prevent slippage, two elastic bands fit around pads up to 64cm wide</li><li>No-snag full-length YKK zipper</li><li>Quilt loops let you customize your sleep system by attaching a Therm-a-rest quilt or blanket over top to add even more warmth</li><li>Stuff sack and storage sack included</li></ul>",
